    <fr:p>We know [<fr:link
type="local"
href="Gro1960b.xml"
addr="Gro1960b"
title="Séminaire de Géométrie Algèbrique">Gro1960b</fr:link>, IV] that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> admits a finite partition into reduced subschemes <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S_i]]></fr:tex> such that each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M\otimes _{\mathcal {O}_S}\mathcal {O}_{S_i}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>flat</fr:em> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
      We can thus suppose that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is flat, and thus that the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_n]]></fr:tex> are flat.
      Finally, we can evidently suppose that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is connected.
      But then [<fr:link
type="local"
href="GD1960.xml"
addr="GD1960"
title="Eléments de Géométrie Algébrique">GD1960</fr:link>, III, §7] there exists an integer <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n_0]]></fr:tex> and a polynomial <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Q]]></fr:tex> such that
      <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[         \operatorname {rank}_{k(s)}M_{ns}\otimes _{\mathcal {O}_{S,s}} k(s)         = Q(n)         \qquad \text {for } n\geqslant  n_0.       ]]></fr:tex>
      Suppose first of all that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P<Q]]></fr:tex>, and so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P(n)\neq  Q(n)]]></fr:tex> for large <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>.
      Then we evidently have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_N=\varnothing ]]></fr:tex> for large enough <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex>, and thus a fortiori the sequence of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_N]]></fr:tex> stabilises.
      In the contrary case, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P(n)\geqslant  Q(n)]]></fr:tex> for large <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, and so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_N=U_{n_0}]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[N\geqslant  n_0]]></fr:tex>, and the sequence of the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_N]]></fr:tex> again stabilises.</fr:p>
